From Doug V Tran Subject Re leaking memory resources in Here's an interesting table showing how much resources an application uses and how much it gives back on shut This is take from Windows User May issue Application Resource Use Resource Not Returned GDI USER GDI USER WinSleuth Gold Word For Windows Lotus Arts and Leters PowerPoint Corel Draw Designer CrossTalk Excel HiJacck Image In Color Pro PIcture Publisher PowerLeads Executive Adobe Type Manager NA NA Skylight The numbers are in percentage and are in a decreasing What does this table tells you if you frequently start and exit a program that doesn't give back all of it's resources then you continually lose these Therefore only open these programs up once and leave them BTW Maybe people can add to this list so we know what application to watch out later Doug